File: Dudu Myeni is accused of writing to Airbus, saying an African leasing company would take over the renting of aircraft from Airbus. JOHANNESBURG - Former SAA chairperson Dudu Myeni is refuting strong evidence by the airline's former Chief Commercial Officer, Sylvain Bosc. A hearing is being held to determine if Myeni should be declared a delinquent director. READ: Court hears how fake letter cost SAA millions of dollars Bosc said Myeni acted fraudulently and lied in an attempt to hijack a lucrative deal between Airbus and SAA to benefit unknown people. Myeni is accused of writing to Airbus saying an African leasing company would take over the renting of aircraft from Airbus. Bosc says the company referred to by Myeni did not exist.